name: super
description:
This card was inspired by my favourite superhero. It captures the moment Clerk Kent transforms from mild mannered reporter...into the most powerful man on the planet! 

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

name: the wedding bouquet
description:
This is the bouquet my beautiful wife was holding when we were married. There is a tradition in the UK where the bride throws it high in the air and whoever catches it, will be the next person to marry. Thankfully...we totally forgot about tradition so I was able to capture the gorgeous floral arrangement (roses and wild flowers) and create this card.

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

description:
FACT: There is nothing cuter than a the high pitched sound of a baby dalek shouting 'exterminate'.

name: pink rose
description:
A classic rosette shaped rose. This photo was taken in the garden of a family friend who is sadly no longer with us. I never asked her what variety of rose it was but, after conducting some research, I believe it to be called 'Mrs John Laing'. It had the most amazingly sweet scent.

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

name: poppy
description:
I love poppies. I love their beauty, their fragility and their fleeting existence. This poppy burst into life on a summer morning in June 2013. I took the picture at 7am...twelve hours later, its petals lay scattered on my lawn. The seed pod left behind was harvested in June 2013 and, from this one flower, another 70 will grow. 

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

name: daisy
description:
This photo was taken in Devon, England, on a very hot day in 2011. The breeze coming in from the sea was a welcome relief for me...and the flowers! Many of the photographs in the flower range were taken at ground level. I had originally intended to capture the flower face on, but then noticed the beautifully intricate pattern on its back and the almost blinding luminosity of its petals. 

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

name: red rose
description:
This was taken whilst watching a game of lawn bowls in a south London park. It is modern rose variety called Alec's Red. It is very fragrant and has a large 15cm flower. It was so beautiful.

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

name: daffy
description:
I live in the UK where a flowering daffodil is a signal that spring has sprung and summer is only a few months away. This photo was taken in a local park on a gorgeous spring morning in April 2013.

Each image is an original design and is printed, hand-cut, then mounted onto your card.

name: like
description: A friend of mine suggested a card with a facebook 'like' button. I created my own version of the thumbs up icon...but the card seemed empty. Using an open source font, I added the text which immediately gave the card a more unique look.

name: dandy
description:
Many people think the dandelion is a pesky weed. I disagree!  The dandelion is a beautiful and fascinating plant.  Its flowers and roots and can be used to treat a variety of ailments, from a fever to an upset tummy, and it has more vitamin and minerals than nearly any other plant. AMAZING.

This photo is of a dandelion that grew in my garden in London, England. The image shows the flower moments before a breath of wind carried the seed pods away.  

This image will be printed, hand-cut and then mounted onto your card.
